tinfour.common

Class ProperEdgeIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • tinfour.common.ProperEdgeIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<IQuadEdge>, java.util.Iterator<IQuadEdge>

    public class ProperEdgeIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<IQuadEdge>, java.util.Iterator<IQuadEdge>
    A wrapper class that provides a way of iterating through edges so that only the proper edges are exposed. In Tinfour, fictious (ghost) edges are indicated using the so-called "ghost vertex", an imaginary vertex that is represented with a null reference. This routine uses the standard Tinfour iterators, but filters out the ghost edges.

      • remove

        public void remove()
        Overrides the default remove operation with an implementation that throws an UnsupportedOperationException. Tinfour requires a specific set of relationships between edges, and removing an edge from an iterator would damage the overall structure and result in faulty behavior. Therefore, Tinfour iterators do not support remove operations.
        Specified by:
        remove in interface java.util.Iterator<IQuadEdge>
